This Proof of Concept (POC) was conducted to evaluate different approaches for generating PDF documents in a Go-based backend system.

The objective was to identify the most suitable solution for generating various types of documents such as invoices, badges, and agreements in a scalable and maintainable manner.

Three different strategies were evaluated:

1. chromedp – Generates PDFs by rendering HTML/CSS using a headless Chrome browser.
2. maroto – A Go-native PDF generation library using a layout-based DSL.
3. pdfcpu – A low-level PDF processing library used here for manual PDF generation.

Each approach was implemented to generate the same set of documents to ensure a fair comparison across:
- Visual fidelity
- Performance
- Maintainability
- Deployment complexity
